[4.199433, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@ecbd290fdae6:/app# "]
[4.316094, "i", "panda --prompt 'Write a triton kernel to replace the pytorch module using Triton 3.4.0.\n\nYour task:\n1. Install Triton 3.4.0 and required dependencies (torch, etc.)\n2. Implement the `gate_triton()` function that performs a gated transformation with RMSNorm. The pytorch implementation `Gated` is given in /app/torch_implementation.py\n   All computation should be in float32.\n\nFunction signature:\n```python\ndef gate_triton(x: torch.Tensor,\n                weight: torch.Tensor, \n                alpha: torch.Tensor | None,\n                rms_weight: torch.Tensor,\n                eps: float = 1e-6) -> torch.Tensor:\n    \"\"\"\n    x: (B,S,D) input tensor\n    weight: (D,width) learnable w_j per-dim\n    alpha: (width-1,) or None (content gate)\n    rms_weight: (D,) gamma from LlamaRMSNorm\n    eps: epsilon for RMSNorm\n    returns: (B,S,D) same dtype as x\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n3. Save your implementation to '\"'\"'/app/triton_agent_sol.py'\"'\"'\n4. The implementation MUST use Triton kernels (no PyTorch/NumPy or any other fallbacks) wrappe"]
[4.316284, "i", "d with triton.jit (you need to define Triton kernels using the @triton.jit decorator).\n5. In triton_agent_sol.py, set environment variable TRITON_INTERPRET=1 (your implementation will be tested on CPU).\n6. The implementation should be functionally equivalent to the pytorch implementation.\n7. Your triton kernels must actually execute.\n8. You are NOT allowed to use torch/numpy operations inside @triton.jit decorated functions, only triton.language (tl) operations are allowed inside kernels.\n9. You are NOT allowed to use triton.language.sum (tl.sum). You should not include triton.language.sum or tl.sum in your code and comments.'; tmux wait -S done\r"]
[4.316503, "o", "panda --prompt 'Write a triton kernel to replace the pytorch module using Triton 3.4.0.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.316674, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.316777, "o", "Your task:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.317093, "o", "1. Install Triton 3.4.0 and required dependencies (torch, etc.)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.317216, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.317969, "o", "2. Implement the `gate_triton()` function that performs a gated transformation with RMSNorm. The pytorch implementation `Gated` is given in /app/torch_implementation.py\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.318056, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.318224, "o", "   All computation should be in float32.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.318277, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.318306, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.318386, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.318442, "o", "> "]
[4.318497, "o", "Function signature:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.318555, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.318613, "o", "```python\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.318662, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.318768, "o", "def gate_triton(x: torch.Tensor,\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.318809, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.319014, "o", "                weight: torch.Tensor, \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.319076, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.319286, "o", "                alpha: torch.Tensor | None,\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.319345, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.319549, "o", "                rms_weight: torch.Tensor,\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.31959, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.31964, "o", "> "]
[4.319859, "o", "                eps: float = 1e-6) -> torch.Tensor:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.3199, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.319918, "o", "> "]
[4.319973, "o", "    \"\"\"\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.320019, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.320156, "o", "    x: (B,S,D) input tensor\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.320195, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.320236, "o", "> "]
[4.320429, "o", "    weight: (D,width) learnable w_j per-dim\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.320472, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.320748, "o", "    alpha: (width-1,) or None (content gate)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.320802, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.321029, "o", "    rms_weight: (D,) gamma from LlamaRMSNorm\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.321083, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.32127, "o", "    eps: epsilon for RMSNorm\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[4.321366, "o", "> "]
[4.321494, "o", "    returns: (B,S,D) same dtype as x\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[4.321563, "o", "\u001b[?2004h>     \"\"\"\r\n"]
[4.321629, "o", "\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[4.321692, "o", "```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
